criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy male or female participant judged by a responsible physician with no
             abnormality identified on a medical evaluation;

          -  Thai, Burmese or Karen ethnicity;

          -  Aged ≥ 18 to <60 years old;

          -  Living in Mae Sot city for the last 12 months;

          -  Willing to participate in the activity and able to give informed consent for
             participating in the study;

          -  Able to tolerate direct mosquito exposure.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of travel in a malaria endemic are (rural village) in the last 12 months, or
             plan to do so during the study;

          -  Medication or condition deemed to interfere with the outcome measure by a responsible
             physician;

          -  Moderate and severe anemia (haemoglobin concentration less than 110 g/L of blood);

          -  Hypersensitivity or anaphylaxis to mosquito bites;

          -  Pregnant women
